Large centers of glaciation are Mount Elbrus and the Bezengi wall (with the Bezengi glacier, 17 km). the plain and the Kura depression, within which are the Alazan-Avtoranskaya valley and the Kura-Araks lowland. In the southeastern part of the Caucasus there are the Talysh mountains (height up to 2492 m) with the adjacent Lenkoran lowland. In the middle and west of the southern part of the Caucasus is the Transcaucasian Highlands , consisting of the ranges of the Lesser Caucasus (the highest point is the city of Aragats, 4090 m) and the Armenian Highlands.